commit.message: debian: Don't install CScreensaver-1.0.gir.

Revert "backup locker: Restore stack management when not activated."

This reverts commit 6b917facf2753552164e669892af929e54dc7834.

This commit led to a regression:

When no windows are visible (all minimized, or no windows at all),
the user would only see a black screen, not the locker.

To reproduce:

- Start the OS and log in
- Don't open any windows
- Close and reopen the lid to trigger a suspend/resume
- See a black screen instead of the locker on resume

This revert fixes that.

commit.message:
cinnamon-screensaver-main.py: Fix application theme provider.

We relied on the return value from Gtk.CssProvider.load_from_data
method to determine whether or not to apply the fallback theme.

The return value itself was deprecated, but still works in Gtk3.
Unfortunately a change was recently made in pygobject that overrides
this method, and since the return value is removed in Gtk4, it
was removed from this override, so is always interpreted as False.

Use try/except instead, as that method can still raise an error
upon failure.

Fixes #446

Ref:
https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/pygobject/-/merge_requests/231

commit.message:
Don't use libaccountsservice, which can block startup.

The only way to initialize an instance for org.freedesktop.Accounts
is synchronously, and will block if it's non-functional. Instead just
make our own dbus proxy which is asynchronous, and can fail without
impacting the screensaver operation (in the worst case missing the
user avatar in the unlock dialog).

commit.message:
Fix stacking issue with the backup window.

Both are override-redirect and ignore stacking. Under some
conditions, the backup locker could end up on top of the
screensaver, even though the screensaver behaves correctly
and is still usable.

Changing window types to get better control isn't a good idea,
as everything still needs to work properly with or without
compositing (cinnamon running). Avoiding painting the window
until it's needed steps around the issue, whether the backup
window ends up above or below the screensaver window.

ref: #424
ref: linuxmint/cinnamon#11632

verification.payload:
tree 10927476e1fb5b22a8a344563da954b46ed1ab84

Fix stacking issue with the backup window.

Both are override-redirect and ignore stacking. Under some
conditions, the backup locker could end up on top of the
screensaver, even though the screensaver behaves correctly
and is still usable.

Changing window types to get better control isn't a good idea,
as everything still needs to work properly with or without
compositing (cinnamon running). Avoiding painting the window
until it's needed steps around the issue, whether the backup
window ends up above or below the screensaver window.

ref: #424
ref: linuxmint/cinnamon#11632

commit.message:
stage: Multiply the stage window by the global scale.

Even though the scale is already accounted for in Gtk/Gdk functions,
muffin can be confused during configuration events like power
management and monitor hotplugging causing breaks in screen coverage.

ref: linuxmint/cinnamon#10879
ref: linuxmint/cinnamon#10998
